{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Abolish the requirement for spousal consent from the Gender Recognition Act 2004",
        "additional_details": "",
        "background": "Currently, the Gender Recognition Act requires married applicants to obtain a spouse\u2019s consent or for the marriage to be ended to receive a full Gender Recognition Certificate. We believe this creates a spousal veto that can undermine individual autonomy and be used to delay legal recognition.",
